### Support Issue API Endpoints

@baseUrl = https://localhost:5001/api
@issueEndpoint = {{baseUrl}}/issue
@categoryEndpoint = {{baseUrl}}/issue-category

### === ISSUE CATEGORY ENDPOINTS ===

### 1. Create a new category
POST {{categoryEndpoint}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Technical Issues",
  "priority": 1
}

### 2. Get all categories
GET {{categoryEndpoint}}

### 3. Get category by ID
GET {{categoryEndpoint}}/1

### 4. Update a category
PUT {{categoryEndpoint}}/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Technical Support",
  "priority": 2
}

### 5. Delete a category
DELETE {{categoryEndpoint}}/1

### === ISSUE ENDPOINTS ===

### 6. Get all categories (from issue endpoint)
GET {{issueEndpoint}}/categories

### 7. Create a new issue
POST {{issueEndpoint}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject": "Cannot access course materials",
  "description": "I'm unable to access the course materials for Computer Science 101. The download link appears to be broken.",
  "categoryId": 1,
  "userId": "user123"
}

### 8. Get all issues
GET {{issueEndpoint}}

### 9. Get issue by ID
GET {{issueEndpoint}}/1

### 10. Get issues by user ID
GET {{issueEndpoint}}/user/user123

### 11. Update an issue
PUT {{issueEndpoint}}/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject": "Updated: Cannot access course materials",
  "status": 1
}

### 12. Update issue status to Closed
PUT {{issueEndpoint}}/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": 2
}

### 13. Delete an issue
DELETE {{issueEndpoint}}/1
